<item>
            <title>[OWB-457] we must not create a SessionContext for static resource reqeusts</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OWB-457</link>
                <project id="12310844" key="OWB">OpenWebBeans</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;we currently trigger the creation of a new session in WebBeansConfigurationListener#requestInitialized. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This leads to unnecessarily creating tons of SessionContexts if a static resource like an image gets requested.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should seek a way to either configurably exclude paths from this mechanism or to only create the SessionContext if a SessionContext gets requested inside the BeanManager&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
