                            <comment id="12914125" author="struberg" created="Thu, 23 Sep 2010 17:53:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Work in progress! This patch introduces a LazySessionContext.&lt;br/&gt;
It will be used instead creating a fully blown Session.&lt;br/&gt;
The &lt;b&gt;real&lt;/b&gt; SessionContext will only be created if a bean get&apos;s requested.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All this stuff needs tough testing though!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12914182" author="kelapure" created="Thu, 23 Sep 2010 19:29:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Mark,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was also coding up a fix for this JIRA issue. I am attaching my patch for this issue which is still under test. &lt;br/&gt;
I took the approach of extending the RequestContext instead of the SessionContext. &lt;br/&gt;
If you see anything useful in my patch please steal it.&lt;br/&gt;
I have done some testing with my patch; however it is still a work in progress.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;--Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Rohit Kelapure&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="12914211" author="struberg" created="Thu, 23 Sep 2010 20:21:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Rohit!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I glimpsed over your patch and it looks good. While my code is smaller, yours is much more straight forward and as such more easy to maintain I think. Will apply it and do a bit testing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;txs and LieGrue,&lt;br/&gt;
strub&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
